A domino is made up of two congruent squares placed side by side. The perimeter of the domino is given as 60 units. The task is to find the area of the domino in square units.Let's represent the domino using LaTeX: egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) rectangle (2,1);\draw (2,0) rectangle (4,1);
ode at (1,0.5) {$l$};
ode at (3,0.5) {$l$};
ode at (2,1.3) {$l$};
ode at (2,-0.3) {$l$};\end{tikzpicture}Here, $l$ represents the length of the shorter side of the domino.

Let $ABCD$ be a unit square. A hyperbola has its foci at the midpoints of $\overline{AB}$ and $\overline{CD},$ and passes through all the vertices of the square. The problem is to compute the distance between the two vertices of the hyperbola. egin{center} egin{tikzpicture}\draw (-1,1) -- (1,1) -- (1,-1) -- (-1,-1) -- cycle;\draw[dotted] (0,-1) -- (-1,1);
ode[above left] at (-1,1) {$A$};
ode[above right] at (1,1) {$B$};
ode[below right] at (1,-1) {$C$};
ode[below left] at (-1,-1) {$D$};
ode[above] at (0,1) {$M$};
ode[below] at (0,-1) {$N$};\draw[scale=1,domain=-2:2,smooth,variable=\x,blue] plot ({\x},{(sqrt(5)-1)/2*sqrt(1+\x*\x)});\draw[scale=1,domain=-2:2,smooth,variable=\x,blue] plot ({\x},{-(sqrt(5)-1)/2*sqrt(1+\x*\x)}); ill (0,(sqrt(5)-1)/2) circle (2pt); ill (0,-(sqrt(5)-1)/2) circle (2pt);\end{tikzpicture}\end{center}
